Editor's note: This live stream has ended. You may watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Nelson Mandela Centre of Memory in Houghton commemorates the death of Nelson Mandela on Tuesday. The centre is marking the 4th anniversary of Madiba's passing.  General Bantu Holomisa will deliver the keynote address. Other speakers include: Professor Njabulo Ndebele – chairperson of the Nelson Mandela Foundation; Sello Hatang – CEO of the Nelson Mandela Foundation; and Minister in the Presidency Jeff Radebe – chairperson of the inter-ministerial committee on Nelson Mandela’s centenary Madiba died at the age of 95 on 5 December 2013. eNCA